'''Ismail Joshua Jakobs''' (born 17 August 1999) is a French-Senegalese<ref name="express.de">{{Cite web|url=https://www.express.de/sport/fussball/1--fc-koeln/-leistungsprinzip-steht-im-vordergrund--striptease---rekord---so-ticken-die-fc-bubis-33639330|title="Leistungsprinzip steht im Vordergrund": Striptease & Rekord&nbsp;– so ticken die FC-Bubis|first1=Jürgen|last1=Kemper|first2=Martin|last2=Zenge|date=19 December 2019|website=Express.de}}{{Dead link|date=February 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]].<ref name="Fix">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/fix-koelns-jakobs-wechselt-zur-as-monaco-865308/artikel|title=Fix: Kölns Jakobs wechselt zur AS Monaco|access-date=12 July 2021|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de}}</ref> Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Senegal football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
===1. FC Köln===
After starting his career at BC Bliesheim, Jakobs joined the youth academy of [[1. FC Köln]] in 2012. In 2017, having progressed through all of the club's youth sides, he was introduced into Köln's [[1. FC Köln II|U21 team]] competing in the fourth-tier [[Regionalliga West]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/ismail-jakobs/spieler|title=Ismail Jakobs|access-date=11 July 2021|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2019–20 Bundesliga|2019–20 season]] Jakobs was promoted to the club's first team by then manager [[Achim Beierlorzer]]. On 8 November 2019, he made his debut appearance in a match against [[TSG Hoffenheim]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rundschau-online.de/sport/1-fc-koeln/nach-remis-gegen-augsburg-die-spieler-des-1--fc-koeln-in-der-einzelkritik-33547744|website=Kölnische Rundschau|title=Nach Remis gegen Augsburg. Die Spieler des 1. FC Köln in der Einzelkritik|date=30 November 2019|access-date=13 December 2019}}{{Dead link|date=January 2026 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref> On 18 December 2019, Jakobs scored his first goal as a professional in a 2–4 victory against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-koeln-2019-bundesliga-4588797/analyse|title=Aus 0:2 mach 4:2&nbsp;– Kölner Wahnsinn in Frankfurt|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|access-date=18 December 2019}}</ref> In March 2020, the club announced that Jakobs' contract had been extended until 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/jakobs-automatische-vertragsverlaengerung-in-koeln-4000000033032/transfermeldung|title=Jakobs: "Automatische" Vertragsverlängerung in Köln|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref> In October of the same year, he signed a further extension keeping him at Köln until July 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/jakobs-verlaengert-der-fc-ist-mein-verein-786769/artikel|title=Jakobs verlängert: "Der FC ist mein Verein"|access-date=9 October 2020|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de}}</ref>

===AS Monaco===
On 12 July 2021, Jakobs was transferred to [[Ligue 1]] side [[AS Monaco]], where he signed a contract until 2026.<ref name="Fix"/> He made his debut for the club in a 2–0 win over [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] in the third qualifying round of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] on 3 August.

On 7 October 2023, he scored his first goal for Monaco against [[Stade de Reims]] during a 3-1 win in Champagne.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Efficace, Monaco reprend son trône ! - Débrief et NOTES des joueurs (Reims 1-3 ASM) |url=https://www.maxifoot.fr/football/article-55626.htm |access-date=2023-10-11 |website=www.maxifoot.fr |language=fr}}</ref>

===Galatasaray===
On 2 September 2024, Jakobs joined Turkish [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on loan from Monaco, until the end of the 2024–25 season, with an obligation to buy after.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/ismail-joshua-jakobsun-transferi-hakkinda/56049|title=Ismail Joshua Jakobs'un transferi hakkında|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=2 September 2024|access-date=2 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/galatasaraya-hos-geldin-ismail-jakobs/56050|title=Galatasaray'a hoş geldin Ismail Jakobs!|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=2 September 2024|access-date=2 September 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
On 21 August 2020, Jakobs was nominated for [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany's under-21 national team]] by manager [[Stefan Kuntz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/wirtz_maina_co_kuntz_beruft_sieben_neue_in_die_u_21-782489/artikel|title=Wirtz, Maina & Co.: Kuntz beruft sieben Neue in die U21|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|access-date=21 August 2020}}</ref> He was a member of the squad that won the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/artikel/nationalmannschaft-u21-star-ismail-jakobs-wird-teamkollege-von-mane/12700377/34240|title=Verbandswechsel! U21-Europameister wird Teamkollege von Mane|language=German|date=18 September 2021|access-date=13 January 2024|website=Sky Deutschland}}</ref>

Jakobs made his debut for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal senior national team]] in 2022, appearing against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] on 24 September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://larepublica.pe/deportes/mundial-qatar-2022/2022/11/19/mundial-qatar-2022-ismail-jakobs-podria-quedar-fuera-de-la-copa-del-mundo-seleccion-senegal-fifa|title=¡Otro bombazo! Senegal podría dejar fuera de Qatar a su 'Byron Castillo'|language=Spanish|date=19 November 2022|access-date=30 December 2023|website=La República}}</ref> He played in all four of Senegal's matches at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] as the nation reached the round of 16 for the first time since its debut in [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/team/squad/_/id/654/league/FIFA.WORLD|title=Senegal Squad|access-date=29 December 2023|website=ESPN UK}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in Senegal's squad for the postponed [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] held in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67840713|title=Afcon 2023: Senegal and Sadio Mane set for defence of title|date=29 December 2023|access-date=29 December 2023|work=BBC Sport Africa}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in Germany, Jakobs is [[Senegalese nationality law|Senegalese]] and [[France|French]] by his father. His mother is German, and he carries her surname. Jakobs holds Senegalese and French nationalities from his father.<ref name="express.de"/>

